Two MOH (Medal of Honor-it's not called Congressional Medal of Honor) nominations that were refused, no lower medal awarded and the records destroyed?  That sounds like a load of bull to me.  Ed, I don't doubt you were a hero, I can believe the 76 decorations, but two MOH nominations in which the records were destroyed, I don't think so.  Nixon awarded a MOH to a Green Beret who earned it in Laos for a rescue.  The incident was so secret that the location was classified, even during the award ceremony, but the medal was awarded anyway despite the location.  Ed, I don't doubt your courage and warrior skill or even your authenticity, but I take the MOH very seriously, and I would not even mention a nomination, I didn't have proof to back up.  Something like that makes a good soldier seem like one of these no good liar vets, which YOU ARE CERTAINLY NOT!!  Instead be proud of those Air Medals, DSC's and the Silver Stars, which most of Warriors of the Air earned and don't lament over something that isn't.  
